  "texts": [
    "In both cases, the first part of the data is affected by un-modelled low frequencies at high SNR, pushing the final mass to larger values.",
    "We also note that in the case of TEOBPM, there is also a bias when starting at later times after the peak.",
    "This is because we are assuming given values of the amplitudes and phases evaluated at the peak time.",
    "Applying them at a different reference time will result in a bias.",
